\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 14, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104fwk1665702962259.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/fwk1665702962259.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/fwk1665702962259.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"fwk1665702962259\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Record Management on SEQ\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"fwk1665702962259__record_management_on_seq_171231\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fwk1665702962259__p_d58226e1_d58227e1_d58228e1\">The table shows the data limits imposed by the SEQ connector:</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"fwk1665702962259__table_d5303e1_d5304e1_d5305e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">SEQ Connector Data Limits</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"fwk1665702962259__table_d5303e1_d5304e1_d5305e1__entry__1\">\n Limits allowed\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"fwk1665702962259__table_d5303e1_d5304e1_d5305e1__entry__2\">\n Amount\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fwk1665702962259__table_d5303e1_d5304e1_d5305e1__entry__1\">\n Fields per record\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fwk1665702962259__table_d5303e1_d5304e1_d5305e1__entry__2\">\n Not applicable: maximum record length = 8192 bytes\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fwk1665702962259__table_d5303e1_d5304e1_d5305e1__entry__1\">\n Length of record\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fwk1665702962259__table_d5303e1_d5304e1_d5305e1__entry__2\">\n 8192 bytes\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fwk1665702962259__table_d5303e1_d5304e1_d5305e1__entry__1\">\n Fields per key\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fwk1665702962259__table_d5303e1_d5304e1_d5305e1__entry__2\">\n Not applicable\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fwk1665702962259__table_d5303e1_d5304e1_d5305e1__entry__1\">\n Amount of indexes\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fwk1665702962259__table_d5303e1_d5304e1_d5305e1__entry__2\">\n Not applicable\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fwk1665702962259__table_d5303e1_d5304e1_d5305e1__entry__1\">\n Maximum length of key\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fwk1665702962259__table_d5303e1_d5304e1_d5305e1__entry__2\">\n Not applicable\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fwk1665702962259__table_d5303e1_d5304e1_d5305e1__entry__1\">\n Maximum length of a field\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fwk1665702962259__table_d5303e1_d5304e1_d5305e1__entry__2\">\n Not applicable: maximum record length = 8192 bytes\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"fwk1665702962259__topic_d38527e1_d38528e1_d38529e1_d38530e1_d38531e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d304440e142\">\n                        \n File Creation\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fwk1665702962259__p_d58232e1_d58233e1_d58234e1\">Files are created on the fly at run time. File names and field names must comply with Uniface naming conventions.Your file names must also comply with the rules of the operating system.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fwk1665702962259__p_d58235e1_d58236e1_d58237e1\">Primary key fields are reproduced in a file of the same name with the prefix <code class=\"ph codeph\">O</code>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"fwk1665702962259__topic_d38532e1_d38533e1_d38534e1_d38535e1_d38536e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d304440e157\">\n                        \n Primary Keys\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fwk1665702962259__p_d58241e1_d58242e1_d58243e1\">All storage formats are allowed for key fields. However, it is not recommended that you use certain storage formats (Boolean, for example) for key fields.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fwk1665702962259__p_d58244e1_d58245e1_d58246e1\">If a sequential file contains a compound primary key, the primary key fields must be contiguous. If the primary key fields are not contiguous, Uniface is unable to convert in either direction and returns the warning <code class=\"ph codeph\">data fetch error</code>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"fwk1665702962259__topic_d38537e1_d38538e1_d38539e1_d38540e1_d38541e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d304440e173\">\n                        \n Indexes\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fwk1665702962259__p_d58250e1_d58251e1_d58252e1\">Sequential files do not have indexes. The SEQ connector maintains indexes internally (that is, in the connector) as soon as a file is accessed. These indexes are maintained on the basis of the conceptual definitions for that file.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fwk1665702962259__p_d58253e1_d58254e1_d58255e1\">The SEQ connector cannot create indexes in sequential files.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/eew1665702619155.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Naming Rules for Uniface Development Objects</a><p>The name of a development object is its unique identifier. When naming development objects, use the allowed syntax for the object name. Avoid using words that are reserved for use within Uniface and your own environment, including the operating system and database.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527702\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527702\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Record Management on SEQ Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 14, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Record Management on SEQ The table shows the data limits imposed by the SEQ connector: Table 1. SEQ Connector Data Limits Limits allowed Amount Fields per record Not applicable: maximum record length = 8192 bytes Length of record 8192 bytes Fields per key Not applicable Amount of indexes Not applicable Maximum length of key Not applicable Maximum length of a field Not applicable: maximum record length = 8192 bytes File Creation Files are created on the fly at run time. File names and field names must comply with Uniface naming conventions.Your file names must also comply with the rules of the operating system. Primary key fields are reproduced in a file of the same name with the prefix O . Primary Keys All storage formats are allowed for key fields. However, it is not recommended that you use certain storage formats (Boolean, for example) for key fields. If a sequential file contains a compound primary key, the primary key fields must be contiguous. If the primary key fields are not contiguous, Uniface is unable to convert in either direction and returns the warning data fetch error . Indexes Sequential files do not have indexes. The SEQ connector maintains indexes internally (that is, in the connector) as soon as a file is accessed. These indexes are maintained on the basis of the conceptual definitions for that file. The SEQ connector cannot create indexes in sequential files. Related Links Naming Rules for Uniface Development Objects The name of a development object is its unique identifier. When naming development objects, use the allowed syntax for the object name. Avoid using words that are reserved for use within Uniface and your own environment, including the operating system and database. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}